OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FCanada experiments with    
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fdecriminalising hard drugs 
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Canada's province of British Columbia  
OL,6, is starting a first-in-the-nation trial
OL,7, decriminalising small amounts of hard  
OL,8, drugs such as cocaine and heroin.      
OL,10,FFrom Tuesday, adults can possess up to 
OL,11,F2.5g of such drugs, as well as         
OL,12,Fmethamphetamine, fentanyl and morphine.
OL,14,FCanada's federal government granted the
OL,15,Frequest by the west coast province to  
OL,16,Ftry out the three-year experiment.     
OL,18,FIt follows a similar policy in the     
OL,19,Fnearby US state of Oregon, which       
OL,20,Fdecriminalised hard drugs in 2020.     
